{"text": "The string of the bow is wrapped once around the spindle, so that it is tight enough not to slip during operation. In a variation called the Egyptian bow drill, the cord is wound around the shaft multiple times, or is fixed to it by a knot or a hole.\n\nThe strap drill is a simpler version, where the bow is absent and the cord is kept taut by pulling the ends with both hands, while moving them left and right at the same time. In the absence of a frame, the thimble is shaped so that it can be held with the chin or the mouth.", "embedding": [0.010470324, 0.007455874, -0.17827782, -0.04298346, 0.06791269, -0.01361938, 0.070697464, -0.033826273, 0.022406716, -0.035383005, -0.08513681, -0.008938383, 0.032090593, -0.0136899855, 0.043070983, -0.021697683, 0.052812174, -0.075274736, 0.021096168, 0.035706993, -0.03037791, -0.008920373, -0.013789964, -0.006590254, 0.05839619, -0.008597648, -0.0026242582, 0.006358207, 0.00014007457, 0.017626964, 0.004237332, -0.013118841, 0.022122128, -0.0474597, -0.052335914, -0.113249995, 0.0065974263, -0.021477144, 0.031999514, 0.038887683, 0.004369144, -0.029772684, -0.008800357, -0.004519129, 0.043055028, -0.053315125, 0.09988608, 0.0154763255, 0.06102459, -0.028895292, 0.04619096, -0.09613441, -0.034332257, -0.049691822, 0.07173464, 0.005316455, 0.08237729, 0.039952543, 0.06332586, 0.006342847, 0.007688559, 0.05267733, -0.03454821, 0.061697606, 0.008057279, 0.0018803123, -0.05694482, 0.068591565, 0.043119986, 0.018500466, 0.037847213, -0.0386549, 0.05734695, 0.01058734, -0.060165662, 0.03236873, -0.042103082, 0.006636796, -0.045873582, 0.015675213, 0.009093723, 0.019853335, 0.010545613, -0.043150105, 0.04232869, -0.025273774, -0.03376959, -0.012364183, -0.043117378, 0.074275404, 0.021619385, 0.016111417, 0.04618739, 0.048278697, -0.057925, 0.01029841, 0.0019216704, 0.009685187, -0.02598715, -0.020993557, -0.020139333, 0.0026128774, -0.026350047, 0.02426001, 0.018511686, 0.044566743, -0.004770086, 0.0029141435, -0.020284386, -0.