{"text": "For use as a fire drill, the shaft should have a blunt end, which is placed into a small cavity of a stationary piece of wood (the fireboard). Turning the shaft with high speed and downward pressure generates heat, which eventually creates powdered charcoal and ignites it forming a small ember.\n\nFor drilling, the lower end of the spindle may be fitted with a hard drill bit that creates the hole by abrasion or cutting.\n\nThe bow lathe used for traditional woodturning uses the same principle as the bow drill.", "embedding": [0.06310382, 0.027467031, -0.17580122, -0.038756423, 0.07250674, -0.0038735853, 0.045199674, 0.01893692, -0.0072978595, -0.054965477, -0.03662331, 0.035599053, 0.043876268, -0.0013936776, 0.0067423913, 0.0023352779, 0.023677355, -0.050759554, 0.055451382, 0.052272677, -0.021951046, -0.020011682, -0.0059383, -0.025692714, 0.041777138, -0.029777242, 0.007103183, 0.008607081, 0.057686392, -0.009596545, 0.010251206, 0.0016587671, -0.03610394, -0.0287698, -0.06956998, -0.12101304, 0.00012636645, -0.029222619, 0.013446574, -0.0035756472, -0.0054070023, -0.03934022, 0.03484153, -0.004788546, 0.02942216, -0.014385502, 0.094558366, -0.029050115, 0.06191578, 0.015915671, 0.08660557, -0.14283703, 0.0045062043, -0.081472985, 0.075275674, 0.0083176615, 0.052265245, 0.021720972, 0.059719983, -0.021423861, -0.010464136, 0.06671761, -0.051564094, 0.058304433, 0.03556585, 0.012895257, -0.046610948, 0.037748754, 0.004967517, -0.00086880854, 0.031747375, -0.018063461, 0.04714375, 0.01358469, -0.06297132, 0.0037835964, -0.012785949, 0.010328874, -0.051592506, 0.045702383, 0.0057380884, -0.014167562, 0.05480429, -0.03202632, 0.022514937, 0.018516732, -0.039096624, 0.01681974, -0.03169616, 0.03189089, 0.036048155, 0.06307314, 0.08419115, 0.06436013, -0.06015048, 0.03281664, 0.016579546, 0.020833733, -0.013798934, -0.02256172, -0.024976235, -0.027820628, 0.0023637402, 0.022112312, 0.017873308, 0.017742727, -0.009849208, 0.004231626, -0.022509895, -0.01742389